{"title_page": "Blank Check with Griffin & David", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{short description|American podcast}}\n{{Infobox podcast\n|title        = Blank Check with Griffin & David\n|image        = [[File:Blank check podcast logo.jpg|250px]]\n|caption      =\n|host         = {{Unbulleted list\n|[[Griffin Newman]] \n|David Sims\n}}\n|language     = English\n|website      = [https://audioboom.com/channel/Blank-Check Blank Check]\n|updates      = Weekly\n|production   = Ben Hosley\n|audio format = Podcast (via streaming or downloadable MP3)\n|began        = {{Start date|2015|3|23}}\n|ended        =\n|num_seasons =\n|num_episodes =\n|runtime = Variable (2-3 hours)\n|genre        = Film\n|cited_for    = \n|cited_as     = \n|provider     = [[AudioBoom]]\n}}\n'''''Blank Check with Griffin & David''''' is a film podcast following the career output of directors who have had significant success and are then offered a figurative ''blank check'' to pursue their passion projects. Most episodes focus on a single movie from the director's filmography.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://audioboom.com/channel/Blank-Check |access-date=August 28, 2019 |title=Blank Check with Griffin & David}}</ref> The show is hosted by ''[[The Atlantic]]'' film critic David Sims and actor [[Griffin Newman]].\n\n''Blank Check'' has been positively reviewed by ''[[Paste Magazine]]'',<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2018/07/blank-check-and-the-intersection-of-comedy-and-cri.html |title=Blank Check and the Intersection of Comedy and Criticism |last=Techler |first=Graham |work=Paste Magazine | date=July 5, 2018 |access-date=August 28, 2019}}</ref> ''[[Decider (website)|Decider]]'',<ref name=\"decider\">{{cite news|url=https://decider.com/2016/01/28/blank-check-is-the-movie-podcast-you-need-to-be-listening-to-especially-if-youre-into-m-night-shyamalan/ |title=\u2018Blank Check\u2019 Is the Movie Podcast You Need to Be Listening To (Especially If You\u2019re Into M. Night Shyamalan) |last=Reid|first=Joe|work=Decider | date=January 28, 2016 |access-date=August 28, 2019}}</ref> and ''[[The A.V. Club]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://aux.avclub.com/griffin-and-david-tackle-inception-this-week-on-blank-c-1798288515 |title=Griffin and David tackle Inception this week on Blank Check\u2019s podcast-in-a-podcast |first1=Mike |last1=Vanderbilt |first2=Rebecca |last2=Bulnes |first3=Becca |last3=James |first4=Randall |last4=Colburn |first5=Zach |last5=Brooke |work=A.V. Club |date=August 14, 2017 |access-date=August 28, 2019}}</ref> The show was included in [[Esquire Magazine|''Esquire'']]'s list of the best 21 podcasts of 2018,<ref>\n{{cite web|url=https://www.esquire.com/entertainment/g19408625/best-podcasts-2018/ |last=Esquire Editors |date=December 27, 2018 |access-date=August 29, 2019 |title=The 21 Best Podcasts of 2018 |website=Esquire}}</ref> as well as on ''Paste Magazine'''s list of the top 30 podcasts of the decade.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2019/11/best-podcasts-of-the-decade-2010s.html|title=The 30 Best Podcasts of the 2010s|last=Jackson|first=Josh|last2=Staff|first2=Paste|date=October 28, 2019|website=pastemagazine.com|language=en|access-date=November 12, 2019}}</ref> It has also been featured in ''[[New York Magazine|Vulture]]'' and ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' as a selection of the week.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.vulture.com/2018/08/this-week-in-comedy-podcasts-las-culturistas-on-blank-check.html |last=Wright |first=Megh |date=August 31, 2018 |title=This Week in Comedy Podcasts: A Blank Check\u2013Las Culturistas Crossover |access-date=August 29, 2019 |website=Vulture}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/tv/must-list-top-lake-deuce-le-carre/?slide=5741569#5741569 |last=EW Staff |title=This Week's Must List: Top of the Lake, The Deuce, and Le Carr\u00e9's Latest |date=September 8, 2017 |access-date=August 29, 2019 |website=Entertainment Weekly }}</ref>\n\nNotable guests have included directors [[David Lowery (director)|David Lowery]], [[Alex Ross Perry]], [[Lulu Wang (filmmaker)|Lulu Wang]], [[Chris Weitz]], comedians [[Demi Adejuyigbe]] and [[Chris Gethard]], and actors [[Peter Serafinowicz]] and [[Paul Scheer]].\n\n==History==\n''Blank Check'' was originally a podcast called ''The Phantom Podcast'' that assessed the ''Star Wars'' prequel films as if in a universe where the other ''Star Wars'' films did not exist. Originally planning to spend 50 episodes on each film, producer Ben Hosley convinced the hosts to only do ten. Having used a lengthy analysis of a filmography as a means of interrogating the director himself, Newman and Sims decided to use a similar approach in reviewing the works of other directors.<ref name=\"decider\" />\n\nOn January 1, 2019, Newman and Sims created a [[Patreon]] page where fans could pay a monthly amount in exchange for extra content. {{As of|March 2020}}, The ''Blank Check'' Patreon was ranked 16th in the podcast category based on the number of paying supporters.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://graphtreon.com/creator/blankcheck |access-date=March 19, 2020 |website=Graphtreon |title=Blank Check with Griffin & David}}</ref>\n\n==Series overview==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n! style=\"padding: 0 8px;\" rowspan=\"2\"| Miniseries\n! style=\"padding: 0 8px;\" rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! style=\"padding: 0 8px;\" rowspan=\"2\"| Director\n! colspan=\"3\"| Initial Release\n|-\n! Episodes\n! First episode\n! Last episode\n|-\n\n | 1\n | The Phantom Podcast\n |rowspan = \"4\"| [[George Lucas]]\n | 11\n | {{Start date|2015|3|23}}\n | {{End date|2015|6|1}}\n|-\n | 2\n | Attack of the Podcast\n | 10\n | {{Start date|2015|6|22}}\n | {{End date|2015|9|8}}\n|-\n | 3\n | Revenge of The Podcast\n | 10\n | {{Start date|2015|9|21}}\n | {{End date|2015|11|30}}\n|-\n | 4\n | The Star Wars Sequels\n | 6\n | {{Start date|2015|12|6}}\n | {{End date|2016|1|11}}\n|-\n | 5\n | Pod Night Shyamacast\n | [[M. Night 